title.narrative: Percentage of project districts that have implemented the “incremental capacity building” system
Percentage of targeted AWCs reporting key nutrition and service delivery indicators using ICT systems every month for the last 3 mon ths
Percentage of Anganwadi Centers (AWCs) in project districts implementing monthly community-based processes focused on nutrition andhealth counselling (at least 5 events in the past 6 months)
Number of project states in which “convergent nutrition action plans” have been developed by the district convergence committees inat least one district
Percentage of targeted AWWs trained on the ICT based management, monitoring and communication system
Percentage of project districts with district resource groups trained to implement the incremental capacity building system
Number of women and children who have received basic nutrition services
People who have received essential health, nutrition, and population (HNP) services
Number of states with strengthened grievance redress system
Number of project states where at least one mid-media campaign was deployed in the past year
Percentage of CBEs implemented in project districts in the last 6 months that focus on community influencers
Percentage of ICDS supervisors who complete at least 60% of mandated supervision visits to AWCs in the last month
Percentage of AWWs in project districts who have completed all online capacity building modules
Percentage of AWWs provided with training on POSHAN Tracker, who – in the last six months – received their monthly performance incentive at least 4 times
Percentage of Block Resource Groups (BRGs) and sectors that conducted at least four monthly learning and review meetings on nutrition knowledge and services in the last six months
Percentage of project districts that operationalised convergent nutrition action plans among those that developed them in the past year
Percentage of AWWs who meet at least 60% of their targeted number of home visits to pregnant/lactating women (PLW) and children under 3 years in the previous month
Percentage of children 6-23 months of age who receive foods from 4 or more food groups
Percentage of AWCs that deliver a minimum set of services at AWCs in the last month
Cumulative number of pregnant/lactating women (PLW) and children under 3 years in project districts reached by ICDS services
Percentage of AWCs in project districts that have implemented at least 4 CBEs focusing on agreed MIYCN themes in the last 6 months
Percentage of children age 6-8 months receiving solid or semi-solid food and breastmilk
Percentage of targeted AWCs reporting using POSHAN Tracker every month for the last six months
ICDS personnel received training on POSHAN Tracker
Cumulative number of (female) children under 3 years in project districts reached by ICDS services
POSHAN Tracker to include a module to auto-generate list of AWWs eligible for performance incentives
